{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix E-RAB Modification Confirm encoding in S1AP successful outcome handler\n\n### Summary\nThe S1AP encoder in the eNB was unable to properly encode E-RABModificationConfirm successful outcome messages due to a missing procedure code handler. When the eNB attempted to send an E-RABModificationConfirm message in response to an MME-initiated E-RAB modification, the encoding would fail with \"Unknown procedure ID\" error, causing the S1AP connection to become unstable.\n\nThe issue manifested as failed E-RAB modification procedures and intermittent S1AP link disruptions when the MME sent E-RAB modification indications that required a confirm response from the eNB.\n\nRoot cause was the absence of S1AP_ProcedureCode_id_E_RABModificationIndication in the successful outcome encoder switch statement, even though E-RABModificationConfirm is a valid successful outcome message according to 3GPP TS 36.413 specification.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/S1AP/s1ap_eNB_encoder.c`: Added missing case for S1AP_ProcedureCode_id_E_RABModificationIndication in s1ap_eNB_encode_successfull_outcome function to handle E-RABModificationConfirm messages\n"
}